In liquid waste, chemical oxygen demand (COD) is the key estimation factor of biogas generation, and it measures the chemical digestible materials in the wastewater. Out of the total COD found in liquid waste, about 70–90% of their values are utilized to generate biogas from anaerobic digestion, particularly for agriculture and agro-processing wastes with various technologies. The treated COD for biogas generation using wastewater is given by Mugodo et al. (2017):10CODtreatedkgyear=TWWDLyear×CODconckgL×80%\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
